BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Mary Poppins (1964)
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260828T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260828T220000
DTSTAMP:20260710T203459Z
UID:occ-1660@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Film Screening
DESCRIPTION:Disney's 1964 classic with Julie Andrews\, preceded by a live 
 concert on the Mighty Allen Theatre Organ.\n\nThe 1964 Disney musical that
  made Julie Andrews a movie star: a practically perfect nanny descends on 
 the Banks children of Edwardian London\, with Dick Van Dyke's chimney swee
 p Bert along for "Chim Chim Cher-ee\," "A Spoonful of Sugar\," and the res
 t. Rated G\, 2 hours 19 minutes. A live pre-show concert on the house's Mi
 ghty Allen Theatre Organ starts thirty minutes before the film. Note: a co
 ncurrent Glover Park Concert closes North and East Park Streets\, so parki
 ng in the Waddell deck is advised.
GEO:33.9536122;-84.5492054
LAST-MODIFIED:20260710T203458Z
LOCATION:The Strand Theatre\, 117 N Park Square
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://thestrand.my.salesforce-sites.com/ticket/#/instances/a0FPs0000
 075V5ZMAU
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Shrek (2001)
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260923T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260923T170000
DTSTAMP:20260710T203459Z
UID:occ-1661@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Film Screening
DESCRIPTION:DreamWorks' 2001 fairy-tale spoof on the big screen — Mike M
 yers' ogre\, Eddie Murphy's Donkey\, 89 minutes\, PG.\n\nThe 2001 DreamWor
 ks comedy that won the first-ever Oscar for Best Animated Feature\, back o
 n a big screen. An ogre who just wants his swamp to himself strikes a deal
  with the fussy Lord Farquaad: rescue Princess Fiona\, get the fairy-tale 
 squatters off his land. Mike Myers voices Shrek in the Scottish accent he 
 insisted on re-recording every line to get\, with Eddie Murphy\, Cameron D
 iaz\, and John Lithgow rounding out the cast\, plus a Smash Mouth-heavy so
 undtrack that dates it precisely and fondly. Loosely based on William Stei
 g's picture book. 89 minutes\, rated PG.
GEO:33.9536122;-84.5492054
LAST-MODIFIED:20260710T203458Z
LOCATION:The Strand Theatre\, 117 N Park Square
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://thestrand.my.salesforce-sites.com/ticket/#/instances/a0FPs0000
 075VwnMAE
END:VEVENT
